contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:27.480 --> 00:31.210
First, we must begin by explaining my profession.

00:33.270 --> 00:37.730
What I most greatly require

00:37.730 --> 00:39.300
is corpses.

00:40.400 --> 00:44.150
1878   London

00:52.510 --> 00:54.560
It was proven that after death

00:54.560 --> 00:59.790
a person's body will lighten by 21 grams compared to their weight while alive.

00:54.560 --> 00:59.790
T/n: A reference to the ideas of early 20th-century American physician Duncan MacDougall.

01:02.090 --> 01:04.540
This is the weight of the soul's essence

01:04.540 --> 01:06.910
or what one might consider the weight of the soul.

01:09.290 --> 01:12.270
By installing an artificial soul essence

01:12.690 --> 01:15.040
into a corpse that has lost its soul

01:15.040 --> 01:17.030
we are able to resurrect the dead.

01:18.290 --> 01:21.680
However, that is a false soul.

01:27.310 --> 01:31.690
Dr. Victor Frankenstein resurrected the first corpse—

01:31.690 --> 01:33.260
The One.

01:34.430 --> 01:36.190
It is said he was able to speak

01:36.540 --> 01:37.900
pursue love

01:38.270 --> 01:40.370
and even harbor murderous intent.

01:41.840 --> 01:43.450
In his despair

01:44.250 --> 01:48.600
he took the technologies he developed— the Memorandum of Victor

01:48.600 --> 01:50.530
and disappeared.

01:53.630 --> 01:55.840
He left us only

01:55.840 --> 01:57.510
imitations of The One

01:57.510 --> 02:01.740
dolls lacking both souls and language.

02:04.130 --> 02:06.270
If The One possessed a soul

02:07.600 --> 02:13.110
if that 21 gram soul could be returned to empty bodies

02:13.960 --> 02:16.190
then could those who have passed away

02:16.860 --> 02:18.590
live once more?

02:27.690 --> 02:28.650
Move.

02:51.100 --> 02:53.200
Can you see me?

02:53.990 --> 02:55.690
Do you recognize me?

03:06.890 --> 03:07.910
Walk.

03:16.360 --> 03:17.590
Stop.

03:20.790 --> 03:23.690
Power output...is working fine.

03:27.520 --> 03:28.310
Reach out.

03:30.100 --> 03:31.390
Take this pen.

03:48.610 --> 03:51.620
Write down every conversation and action.

03:53.230 --> 03:56.020
I hope this will become your soul.

03:58.400 --> 04:01.130
Welcome back, Friday.

03:58.400 --> 04:01.120
T/n: A reference to the character in <i>Robinson Crusoe</i>.

04:09.000 --> 04:12.710
Now, just prior to the turn of the 20th century

04:13.390 --> 04:17.459
corpse technologies are already able to control a nation's fate.

04:20.470 --> 04:26.910
When Dr. Victor Frankenstein succeeded in resurrecting the dead 100 years ago

04:28.560 --> 04:33.370
people feared and detested resurrection

04:33.370 --> 04:38.080
and steadfastly rejected corpse technology.

04:41.680 --> 04:45.660
The earliest to accept corpses were women.

04:47.350 --> 04:49.560
If corpses were to act as soldiers,

04:49.560 --> 04:54.480
they would not have to lose their husbands and sons to war.

04:56.300 --> 05:02.020
The world realized the value of corpse technologies for military affairs

05:02.020 --> 05:05.290
and began to strongly push the development of corpse technology forward.

05:10.140 --> 05:12.250
The military technology born amidst this

05:12.250 --> 05:14.080
also enabled civilian uses.

05:14.080 --> 05:17.080
It has throroughly changed people's everyday lives.

05:19.770 --> 05:23.930
Artificial soul essences, made from repeated simulations by analytical engines

05:23.930 --> 05:26.650
and recorded onto punch cards

05:26.650 --> 05:28.750
have been named "Necroware."

05:29.500 --> 05:37.020
They are making optimizations for coachmen, housekeepers, laborers, and various fields of work.

05:44.090 --> 05:47.480
In the living world, corpses increase with each passing day.

05:47.480 --> 05:49.500
Even now, it is hardly an overstatement

05:49.500 --> 05:54.170
to say that corpses are the backbone of the world economy.

05:57.600 --> 06:01.630
At the once frightening fortress, the Tower of London

06:04.300 --> 06:06.640
here, corpse engineers

06:06.640 --> 06:09.490
improve Necroware day after day,

06:09.490 --> 06:13.970
endlessly supplying updates to the corpses of the world

06:14.840 --> 06:18.530
by means of the analytical engine of exceptional calculation capabilities

06:18.530 --> 06:21.460
the Charles Babbage.

06:18.530 --> 06:21.460
T/n: An English polymath and "father of the computer."

06:27.290 --> 06:30.760
This is a tale of corpses.

06:32.460 --> 06:37.860
